    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I wrote a tool to automatically add and remove new services to the popular <a href=\"https://github.com/bastienwirtz/homer\">Homer dashboard</a>. Homer Service Discovery is available over on GitHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery\">calvinbui/homer-service-discovery</a>.</p>\n<!-- more -->\n<h2 id=\"the-idea\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-idea\" aria-label=\"the idea permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Idea</h2>\n<p>The initial idea came from my personal experience. Adding, changing or removing a self-hosted service also required updating the Homer dashboard configuration. I wanted to automate this similar to how Traefik would reverse proxy any new containers using its labels.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/fe4d8/dashboard.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 91.07981220657277%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"dashboard\"\n        title=\"dashboard\"\n        src=\"/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/d6170/dashboard.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/53f68/dashboard.png 213w,\n/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/df70d/dashboard.png 425w,\n/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/d6170/dashboard.png 850w,\n/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/12c14/dashboard.png 1275w,\n/static/d5432fdeeedc336ed200a058cd9bf7ef/fe4d8/dashboard.png 1388w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"about\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#about\" aria-label=\"about permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>About</h2>\n<p>The application is written in Golang and is free and open-source including the CI and release process on <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/actions\">GitHub Actions</a>.</p>\n<p>I made it available in multi-arch (x86_64, ARM64 and ARMv7) so all Homer users can use it. It is available as static binary files on the <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/releases\">GitHub release page</a> or Docker images on <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/pkgs/container/homer-service-discovery\">GitHub's Container registry</a> using <a href=\"https://github.com/goreleaser/goreleaser\">goreleaser</a>.</p>\n<p>More information, including how to use it, can be found on the <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/blob/master/README.md\">project's README file</a>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/49379/repo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 47.41784037558685%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"repo\"\n        title=\"repo\"\n        src=\"/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/d6170/repo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/53f68/repo.png 213w,\n/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/df70d/repo.png 425w,\n/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/d6170/repo.png 850w,\n/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/12c14/repo.png 1275w,\n/static/1f24657c2e4aa6996c39e58fe97474b9/49379/repo.png 1395w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"contributing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contributing\" aria-label=\"contributing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contributing</h2>\n<p>The project meets the <a href=\"https://opensource.guide/\">recommended community standards</a> for open source projects with the following resources:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md\">Code of conduct</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\">Contributing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/blob/master/LICENSE\">License</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/tree/master/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE\">Issue templates</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery/blob/master/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md\">Pull request template</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"final-thoughts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#final-thoughts\" aria-label=\"final thoughts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Final Thoughts</h2>\n<p>Features I'd like to add over time include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creating new Services</li>\n<li>Restarting/reloading Homer to clear its cache</li>\n<li>Reading Traefik for an item's URL</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once again, the project is available on GitHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/homer-service-discovery\">calvinbui/homer-service-discovery</a>.</p>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"I wrote a tool to automatically add and remove new services to the popular Homer dashboard. Homer Service Discovery is available over onâ€¦","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/calvin.me/calvin.me/master/posts/2021/2021-08-07-homer-service-discovery/index.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Homer Service Discovery","categories":["Programming"],"tags":["homer","dashboard","golang"],"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":null,"extension":"svg","publicURL":"/static/7d39574a0fa14948df2c0cd9711f21f4/thumbnail.svg"}}}},"pageContext":{"filter":"/^.*\\/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-homer-service-discovery\\/.*$/"}},
